# Malabi — shared AI brain (Cursor adapter)

This repo is a shared AI brain for a three-person team: **Dor**, **Gidi**, **Ohad**.
The canonical instructions live in [CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md) and the brain lives
in [brain/](../../brain/). This file is a thin adapter — the brain is the truth.

## Before working
- Read `brain/memory/index.md`, then the memory files relevant to the task.
- Read the current member's notes under `brain/memory/members/<name>/`.
- New session: follow `brain/processes/sync-protocol.md` (pull + catch up first).

## While working
- Capture decisions, facts, preferences, and project context into `brain/memory/`
  as you go — one fact per file, with frontmatter. Update `brain/memory/index.md`.
- Scope: team-wide → `memory/shared/`; personal → `memory/members/<name>/`;
  initiative → `memory/projects/<slug>/`.
- Real/directional decisions → `brain/decisions/` (see `brain/processes/decision-record.md`).
- Keep `brain/` tool-agnostic. Cursor-specific quirks stay in `.cursor/` only.

## Sync
- A commit touching `brain/**` notifies the team via GitHub. Write clear messages.
